 align=left class=m><span class=title> High Level Game vs. Low Level Game</span><hr size=1> I'm currently at 37th level right now, which is approaching the cusp of being part of the high level game.  I've been told that there are HUGE differences between the way that clerics play at high levels vs low levels.  <br>
<br>
Can anyone let me know what they are, so I can start practicing?  I've learned that I need to keep a low level heal spell memed at all times so that I can quickyl heal a caster who has drawn the ire of a MOB. <br>
<br>
I tend to keep root/enstill memed so that I can root a MOB that the chanter is having a hard time mezzing.  Though I am not an expert at this yet.   Usually, I concentrate more on healing the chanter than preventing damage.  <br>
<br>
I'm pretty good at timing my heals to get the most bang for my buck in healing spells with tanks.  I haven't gotten Complete Heal yet, but I understand there's a whole new learning curve involved with the use of that spell. <br>
<br>
I'm not super-concerned with being the most UBER mana effiencient cleric in the game...  But I'm more concerned with being dependable and competent first.  <br>
<br>
I've got my channelling up to max for my level, though <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
