</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulashannavalrynn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lashanna Valrynn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif BORDER=0> at: 8/22/01 10:35:45 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udrakarisoulfist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Drakari Soulfist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(8/24/01 9:10:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: High Level Game vs. Low Level Game</span><hr size=1> As far as Cheal goes you might wanna talk to your tank too.  Sometimes they don't want to be healed till they reach a certain point. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uf98hfr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>f98hfr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(8/25/01 5:18:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: High Level Game vs. Low Level Game</span><hr size=1> Warriors like to cripple, CH shall land when they have 1-10 hps left. Try it out <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
/Quarken<br>
54 cleric <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uisyssreigns.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Isyss Reigns</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(8/25/01 11:59:28 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: High Level Game vs. Low Level Game</span><hr size=1> Another thing that might help, is learn to fight. Solo.<br>
<br>
Soloing may not be the best thing for a cleric, even though we can solo undead, and other mobs with low hps, but soloing can prepare you take a chance on being hit. How to handle getting pounded on and how to be calm when its happening. Its very important NOT to panic. This strategy also helps you see how the mob hits you and avoid being interupted when you cast that heal. Once you see and know how the mobs hits, you are morelikely to get your heals off while you are being hit. Remember, if you are knocked back from a hit while starting to cast, GO BACK to where you started the cast and YOU WILL regain your concentration on your cast, however, you must be aware of how you are being hit, how much dmg you can take, and the location you are standing incase you are moved by the mob.<br>
<br>
When in group, I have always maintain a calm behavior when a mob starts beating on me after I just dropped what the mob considers a big (agro) heal. This gives the enchanter time to mez the adds. Its very important you buff yourself exactly the same way as your tanks. So you are timed with them when thier buffs are off, that way, you wont lose so much mana in consecutively healing them cause all of a sudden their health is dropping too fast.<br>
<br>
When using root and stun, your lowest level works far better and less mana. I use this to keep a mob off the enchanter again, so he/she is safe to mez. <br>
<br>
/assist key. tanks are not the only ones who uses this key. I use this for different types of purpose. I assist the enchanter as to know who they are trying to mez, if it mez doesnt stick the first time, its faster for me to root that mob if more than one comes along.  <br>
<br>
Faster heal comes along with hot keys. Use hot keys on almost all of your heals and the players on your group. I use keys to target a player and another key for heal/root/stun.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Isyss Reigns<br>
57 Templar<br>
Guildmistress, Sacred Valor</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udonord.showPublicProfile?language=EN>donord</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(8/26/01 7:15:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: High Level Game vs. Low Level Game</span><hr size=1> sweetest thing about velious dragons which is ultimately where the high end game .. well ends .. is that you don't have time to tell yourself to remain calm when you catch aggro.<br>
